Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
getRouteMode(25.10)                                        getRouteMode(25.10)

Name
       getRouteMode  -  Returns  information about the specified  Early Global
       Route mode parameter in the Innovus log file and the console

Syntax
       getRouteMode

       [-help]

       [-earlyGlobalEffortLevel]

             [-earlyGlobalHonorMsvRouteConstraint]

       [-earlyGlobalNumTracksPerClockWire]

        [-earlyGlobalReverseDirection]

       [-earlyGlobalRoutePartitionAllowFeedthru]

        [-earlyGlobalRoutePartitionHonorFence]

        [-earlyGlobalRoutePartitionHonorPin]

        [-earlyGlobalRoutePartitionPinGuide]

       [-earlyGlobalRouteSecondPG]

       [-earlyGlobalRouteSelectedNetsOnly]

       [-earlyGlobalRouteStripeLayerRange]

       [-earlyGlobalSecondPGMaxFanout]

        [-quiet]

       [-nonDefault]

       Returns information about the specified  Early Global Route mode  para-
       meter  in  the Innovus log file and the console. The following informa-
       tion is returned:

              * Parameter name

              * Current value

              * Type (Boolean, string, and so on)

              * Whether the current value was set by user

       If you do not specify a parameter, the  software  displays  information
       for all of the Early Global Route mode parameters.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each getRouteMode parameter. For a detailed  de-
              scription  of the command and all of its parameters, use the man
              command: man getRouteMode

       -nonDefault
              Displays the current settings that are not default settings.

       <parameter_names>
              Displays information for the specified parameters. You can spec-
              ify one or more parameters. See setRouteMode for descriptions of
              the Early Global Route parameters you can specify.

       -quiet Displays the current settings for the  specified  parameters  in
              Tcl  list format only. If you specify -quiet without any parame-
              ters,  the  software  displays  the  current  settings  of   all
              setRouteMode parameters in Tcl list format.

Examples
              * The  following  command  displays  the current setting for the
                -earlyGlobalNumTracksPerClockWire parameter:

                      getRouteMode -earlyGlobalNumTracksPerClockWire

                The software displays the following information:

                      -earlyGlobalNumTracksPerClockWire 0  #  int,  default=0,
                min=0, max=8

                 0

              * The  following  command  displays  the current setting for the
                -earlyGlobalRoutePartitionPinGuide
                     parameter:

                      getRouteMode -earlyGlobalRoutePartitionPinGuide

                The software displays the following information:

                -earlyGlobalHoutePartitionPinGuide true # bool, default=true

                 {earlyGlobalRoutePartitionPinGuide true}

Related Information
              * setRouteMode

              * earlyGlobalRoute

              * Using Early Global Route for Congestion  and  Timing  Analysis
                chapter in the Innovus User Guide

